The paper deals with the problem of finding optimal coalition structures in Weighted Graph Games, which is a subfield of cooperative game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with combinatorial problems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
